.SH NAME
dotty-brewfile-dump - Snapshot the installed brews into the Brewfile.


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBdotty brewfile dump [--all] [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Write the currently installed brews into the Brewfile. By default only
formulae, casks, Mac App Store apps, and Flatpaks are dumped; --all includes
every type brew bundle knows (taps, vscode, go, cargo, uv, krew, npm).
Overwriting an existing Brewfile asks first.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--all\fP[=false]
	dump every entry type brew bundle supports

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for dump


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--profile\fP=""
	profile to operate on (defaults to the active profile)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  dotty brewfile dump
  dotty brewfile dump --all
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBdotty-brewfile(1)\fP
